    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>LinkText is case sensitive. Therefore if you have two links with different cases then they will be two different elements independent of each other.  Your example code seems incorrect to me. The list below will never ever contain a link with text 'LINKTEXT' so the 'else' part is irrelevant and not required.</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;WebElement&gt; list = driver.findElements(By.linkText(\"Linktext\"));\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 25825294,
      "reputation" : 1,
      "user_id" : 19563584,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AItbvmnWxISRCTcqUL_TLCl5Yur6ClsKSPrHJiU2_guy=k-s256",
      "display_name" : "kshitij rastogi",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/19563584/kshitij-rastogi"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1658036012,
    "last_edit_date" : 1658036012,
    "creation_date" : 1658003533,
    "answer_id" : 73007476,
    "question_id" : 8385459,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>This will definitely help, as it worked for me</p>\n<pre><code>List&lt;WebElement&gt; els = driver.findElements( By.xpath( &quot;.//a[@href!='']&quot; ) );\n    for ( WebElement el: els ) {\n        if ( el.getText().toLowerCase().equals( bookDetails.getBookName().toLowerCase() ) ) {\n           el.click();\n           break;\n        }\n    }\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 26315879,
      "reputation" : 36,
      "user_id" : 19978672,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AFdZucp-RL_ByBjPUAAs_H7b4aO4jZ4fvKLdvHmGYGSE0a0=k-s256",
      "display_name" : "GabrielFethi",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/19978672/gabrielfethi"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
